"@RandomFFUser @BillStewart415 @mozilla @firefox What about the network operators choice? DNS is in my control plane. My approval must be sought, and will not in this case be granted."

"@BillStewart415 @RandomFFUser @mozilla @firefox Network operators use DNS firewalls to prevent malicious domains from resolving. Only we know what our threats are. Mandatory outsourcing to cloudflare should not be forced upon us. Why did Mozilla make it hard to block their new DNS protocol?"

"@RandomFFUser @BillStewart415 @mozilla @firefox How would I enforce an Enterprise only FF policy? The non Enterprise FF with it's built in DNS would still work and would still bypass my firewall. Are you victim shaming here? Shall I tell you how I was dressed when the attack began?"

"@BillStewart415 @RandomFFUser @mozilla @firefox you're almost there. an enterprise FW will be _transparent by design_ to FF's new CF-based DNS. so any BYOD is now a mole in my network, an outpost for bad guys. what i will have to do is blackhole CF itself, or at least, the parts that want to serve DNS behind my FW. 1/2"

"@BillStewart415 @RandomFFUser @mozilla @firefox which again begs the question: why is mozilla going to war against me? the DNS is part of the internet's control plane. i will NOT NOT NOT outsource it. (neither should you but that should be your decision not mine and not mozilla's and not cloudflare's). 2/2"

"@xxdesmus @BillStewart415 @RandomFFUser @mozilla @firefox this misses the point. if someone BYOD's into my company or home network, and FF is already using CF before it got there, then the user is effectively opening a VPN endpoint inside my perimeter. why is Moz making this risk _hard to block_? (that's why it's a war on sysadmins.)"

"@RandomFFUser @xxdesmus @BillStewart415 @mozilla @firefox this misses the point. if someone BYOD's into my company or home network, and FF is already using CF before it got there, then the user is effectively opening a VPN endpoint inside my perimeter. why is Moz making this risk _hard to block_? "@xxdesmus @BillStewart415 @RandomFFUser @mozilla @firefox Not fud. This protocol is intentionally hard to block. Moz should fix that before adoption in FF."
"@xxdesmus @BillStewart415 @RandomFFUser @mozilla @firefox Good for you. I will be part of the team dealing with the new strength this will add to the dark side. We won't envy each other."
